Hemp Seed Waffles
  --Julie Morris

1 1/4 c almond milk
1 1/2 tsp apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp chia seed powder
1/2 tsp vanilla
1 c whole wheat flour
2 tbsp coconut palm sugar
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
2 tbsp safflower oil + more for waffle iron
3 tbsp hemp seeds

In a small bowl, whisk together the milk, vinegar, chia powder, nad vanilla. Let stand for 10 min. In a medium bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Add the milk mixture, oil, and hemp seeds, and stir until just combined - do not over mix. Heat the waffle iron; once hot, brush lightly with oil. Pour 1/2 c of batter (depending on size of waffle iron) and cook for 5-7 min or until waffles are golden and crispy. Serve immediately or store in an oven warmed to 250F.
